## Cost of Action vs Cost of Inaction

Every at-risk flight has two cost paths. The dispatcher decides which one the airline pays.

**Doing nothing:** the delay escalates through the brackets, accumulating operating costs, network propagation, EU261 obligations, and eventually cancellation costs.

**Acting early:** each bracket has defined interventions with known costs:

| Bracket | Intervention Cost (EUR) |
|---|---|
| 0 | 0 |
| 1 | 250–700 |
| 2 | 450–1,250 |
| 3 | 2,500–9,500 |
| 4 | 8,000–25,000 |

